# Solution
############################################################

BEGIN_PGML_SOLUTION
A line's standard form is [`Ax+By=C\text{.}`] We need to move [`x`] and [`y`] terms to the same side of the equal sign.

[```\newcommand{\addright}[1]{{\highlight{{{}+#1}}}}\newcommand{\multiplyleft}[2][\cdot]{{\highlight{{#2#1{}}}}}\newcommand{\amp}{&}
\begin{aligned}
y\amp=-\frac{[$a]}{[$b]}x+[$c]\\
\multiplyleft{[$b]}y\amp=\multiplyleft{[$b]}\left(-\frac{[$a]}{[$b]}x+[$c]\right)\\
[$b]y\amp=[$b]\left( -\frac{[$a]}{[$b]}x \right)+[$b]([$c])\\
[$b]y\amp=-[$a]x+[$bc]\\
[$b]y\addright{[$a]x}\amp=-[$a]x+[$bc]\addright{[$a]x}\\
[$s1]\amp=[$bc]
\end{aligned}
```]

END_PGML_SOLUTION

